**Eligibility for the Quota : Telangana Management Quota-Cat B-Unreserved**  

**<u>CAT-B</u>**

All India Basis

**<u>CAT B-ArmyWards</u>**

1. Children of serving Army personnel with minimum 10 years continuous service in the Army (or)
2. Children of ex Army personnel granted/awarded regular pension, liberalized family pension, family pension or disability pension at the time of their superannuation, demise, discharge, release medical board/invalided medical board. This includes wards of recruits medically boarded and granted disability pension (or)
3. Children of ex Army personnel (discharged or released after ten years service

Also  
**Adopted/Step children and children of Remarried Widows**  
i) Adopted Child of Army personnel if adopted at least five years prior to seeking admission  
ii) Step Children are eligible provided they are born from a wedding where at least one parent belonged to the Army who is other wise eligible  

Also the below special cases  
i) Wards of only those ex-Army medical officers/Army Dental Corps officers presently serving with Indian Navy or Indian Air Force who have served with the Army for at least 10 years
ALSO from **Army Postal Services (APS), Military Nursing Services (MNS) and TA (Territorial Army)**  
i) Children of APS Personnel classified as ex-servicemen as per Govt. of India, Ministry of Defence letter No 9 (52)/88D (Res) dated 19 Jul 1989.
ii) Children of those APS personnel who are on deputation and who have put in 10 years of service in the Army.  
iii) Children of APS personnel, who are directly recruited into APS who have completed 10 years of service and of those who as per their terms and conditions of service, retired from APS without reversion to P&T Department after completing their minimum pensionable service of which 10 years was in the Army  
iv) Children of only those members of MNS who have 10 years’ service as regular members of MNS or are in receipt of pension from the Army.
v) Children of only those TA Personnel who have completed 10 years of embodied service.  

(Son <25 years as on Dec 31 of the admission year (Dec 31 2024 for 2024-25, Daughters - On marriage or employment whichever is earlier)

quotas.name: Telangana Management Quota-Cat B-Local
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Telangana Management Quota-Cat B-Local** 

**<u>OU Local Candidates eligible (Tel Local)</u>** - Any one of the below

1. Studied the last 4 years in the State of Telangana before first appearing XII (or)
2. Resided the last 4 years in the State of Telangana before first appearing XII (in case they do not fall under 1) and have studied less than 4 years in Telangana)
3. Studied for 7 years across the state (in this scenario "State" could be the undivided state of Tel/AP too) in 2 or more local areas - then he/she is Local where he/she has studied for the longer period (if 2 or more periods are same, the last local area where studied is considered)
4. Did not study for 7 years across the state but has resided across different local areas in the state (in this scenario "State" could be the undivided state of Tel/AP too) in 2 or more local areas - then he/she is local where he/she has resided for the longer period (if 2 or more periods are same, the last local area where resided is considered)

quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Telangana Management Quota-Cat B-Unreserved**  

**<u>CAT-B</u>**

All India Basis

**<u>CAT B-ArmyWards</u>**

1. Children of serving Army personnel with minimum 10 years continuous service in the Army (or)
2. Children of ex Army personnel granted/awarded regular pension, liberalized family pension, family pension or disability pension at the time of their superannuation, demise, discharge, release medical board/invalided medical board. This includes wards of recruits medically boarded and granted disability pension (or)
3. Children of ex Army personnel (discharged or released after ten years service

Also  
**Adopted/Step children and children of Remarried Widows**  
i) Adopted Child of Army personnel if adopted at least five years prior to seeking admission  
ii) Step Children are eligible provided they are born from a wedding where at least one parent belonged to the Army who is other wise eligible  

Also the below special cases  
i) Wards of only those ex-Army medical officers/Army Dental Corps officers presently serving with Indian Navy or Indian Air Force who have served with the Army for at least 10 years
ALSO from **Army Postal Services (APS), Military Nursing Services (MNS) and TA (Territorial Army)**  
i) Children of APS Personnel classified as ex-servicemen as per Govt. of India, Ministry of Defence letter No 9 (52)/88D (Res) dated 19 Jul 1989.
ii) Children of those APS personnel who are on deputation and who have put in 10 years of service in the Army.  
iii) Children of APS personnel, who are directly recruited into APS who have completed 10 years of service and of those who as per their terms and conditions of service, retired from APS without reversion to P&T Department after completing their minimum pensionable service of which 10 years was in the Army  
iv) Children of only those members of MNS who have 10 years’ service as regular members of MNS or are in receipt of pension from the Army.
v) Children of only those TA Personnel who have completed 10 years of embodied service.  

(Son <25 years as on Dec 31 of the admission year (Dec 31 2024 for 2024-25, Daughters - On marriage or employment whichever is earlier)
